# REST API Design

## API Guidelines
- ✅ Follow REST resource naming guidelines
- ✅ Follow best practices for REST API design
- ✅ Use appropriate HTTP status codes
- ✅ Provide meaningful error responses
- ✅ Document API endpoints clearly

## NestJS Guidelines

> **Note**: For comprehensive NestJS patterns, architecture, and best practices, see [Backend and Developer API Development Guidelines](nest-guidelines.mdc).

### Basic Naming Conventions
- ✅ Use appropriate suffixes:
  - Services: `Service` suffix, `.service.ts`
  - Controllers: `Controller` suffix, `.controller.ts`
  - Modules: `Module` suffix, `.module.ts`
- ✅ Name microservice modules after service
  ```typescript
  // file-processor.module.ts
  export class FileProcessorModule {}
  ```

